    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I've found myself confused on when I need to use `instantsearch.helper` and when I need to use the shallow-clone of it in `searchFunction`.\r\n\r\nBecause the `searchFunction` param is just a shallow clone with `.search()`, if I need any other methods (e.g. `setQueryParameter`), I need to use `instantsearch.helper`. However, once I actually `.search`, I need to use the helper from the `searchFunction` param, or the search won't work.\r\n\r\nHere's an example. I want to prevent initial searching, listen for a map event and `setQueryParameter`, and then search. To do this, I have to juggle between both of the helpers, which seems icky and confusing.\r\n\r\n```\r\nvar myMap = Leaflet.map('my-map');\r\nvar clonedHelper;\r\n\r\nvar instantSearch = new InstantSearch({\r\n  searchFunction: (helper) => {\r\n    clonedHelper = helper;\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n\r\nmap.on('moveend', (event) => {\r\n  instantSearch.helper.setQueryParameter('insideBoundingBox', '...');\r\n  clonedHelper.search();\r\n\r\n  // Doesn't work\r\n  // instantSearch.helper.search();\r\n});\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2017-02-14T13:10:53Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1924#issuecomment-279703066",
