  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @timkelty Actually we failed you here, we are not providing enough resources for the kind of use case you have. The correct way (as instantsearch.js is designed) is to create a custom widget for you map component:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nvar mapWidget = {\r\n  init: function({helper}) {\r\n    this.map = Leaflet.map('my-map');\r\n    map.on('moveend', (event) => {\r\n      helper.setQueryParameter('insideBoundingBox', '...').search();\r\n    });\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI hope this will help you.",
